      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e There\u0027s not too much to be done at this point, but there\u0027s no symbolic links on OS_FUCHSIA even though it defines OS_POSIX, so perhaps you could LOG/TODO/add an untested #if arm here.\n\nVery interesting! Is that the permanent state of affairs for Fuchsia: no symbolic links forever, as an intentional design sort of thing?\n\nIf that’s so, I didn’t really want to leave things in a state where this would always disable the tests, because the tests wouldn’t ever make any sense. So I just avoided defining all of the symbolic link handling and tests on OS_FUCHSIA altogether. Sound good?",
      "parentUuid": "122176c5_c3e08cc7",
      "revId": "43b5ce085047bd00e2f705da9c7524641d18b8b7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
